webpackJsonp([424216785064808e4],{"./node_modules/json-loader/index.js!./.cache/json/css-css-3-gradients.json":function(n,s){n.exports={data:{markdownRemark:{html:'<h2>CSS3 Gradients</h2>\n<p>Css3 lets you use gradients instead of solid colours. A gradient is one colour merging into another one. </p>\n<div class="gatsby-highlight">\n      <pre class="language-css"><code>    <span class="token selector">.linear-gradient</span> <span class="token punctuation">{</span> \n       <span class="token property">background</span><span class="token punctuation">:</span> <span class="token function">linear-gradient</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span>to right, red , yellow<span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span> <span class="token comment" spellcheck="true">/*this is example below*/</span>\n     <span class="token punctuation">}</span>\n     <span class="token selector">.circle-gradient</span> <span class="token punctuation">{</span> \n       <span class="token property">background</span><span class="token punctuation">:</span> <span class="token function">radial-gradient</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span>circle, red , yellow<span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>\n     <span class="token punctuation">}</span>\n   \n</code></pre>\n      </div>\n<p><img src="https://ejke.github.io/else/linear_gradient.png" alt="Image of red to yellow gradient example - towards right"></p>\n<p>The syntax is <br/>\n<i>background: linear-gradient(direction, color-stop1, color-stop2, …);</i><br/>\n<i>background: radial-gradient(shape size at position, start-color, …, last-color);</i></p>\n<!--This is a stub. <a href=\'https://github.com/freecodecamp/guides/tree/master/src/pages/css/css3-gradients/index.md\' target=\'_blank\' rel=\'nofollow\'>Help our community expand it</a>.-->\n<!--<a href=\'https://github.com/freecodecamp/guides/blob/master/README.md\' target=\'_blank\' rel=\'nofollow\'>This quick style guide will help ensure your pull request gets accepted</a>.-->\n<!-- The article goes here, in GitHub-flavored Markdown. Feel free to add YouTube videos, images, and CodePen/JSBin embeds  -->\n<p><b>CSS3 Gradients</b> let you display smooth transitions between 2 or more colors.</p>\n<h4>More Information:</h4>\n<!-- Please add any articles you think might be helpful to read before writing the article -->\n<p>MDN Documentation: <a href=\'https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/gradient\' target=\'_blank\' rel=\'nofollow\'>MDN</a></p>\n<p><a href=\'https://www.w3schools.com/css/css3_gradients.asp\' target=\'_blank\' rel=\'nofollow\'>W3 schools</a>.</p>',fields:{slug:"/css/css3-gradients/"},frontmatter:{title:"CSS3 Gradients"}}},pathContext:{slug:"/css/css3-gradients/"}}}});
